and if you're not using that service,

00:18:59.020 --> 00:19:02.790
disable it, just kind of like I said
about the interfaces.

00:19:02.950 --> 00:19:07.070
We always note within OS X that
we definitely don't want customers

00:19:07.070 --> 00:19:11.670
to be using the insecure versions
of things like Telnet and others.

00:19:11.970 --> 00:19:14.710
That's why we, by default, use SSH,
right?

00:19:14.790 --> 00:19:16.790
That's the way it's configured in OS X.

00:19:16.900 --> 00:19:21.770
SSH, secure copy,
secure remove for securely erasing data.

00:19:21.900 --> 00:19:24.020
So again,
if you aren't using the service,

00:19:24.020 --> 00:19:24.750
disable it.

00:19:24.850 --> 00:19:28.830
Some organizations will go as
