Again, some of these seem so
simple and so natural,

00:22:21.890 --> 00:22:26.110
but we always want to be sure that
folks are aware of and fully leverage

00:22:26.500 --> 00:22:32.000
the additional updates and advancements
of security updates coming from Apple.

00:22:33.340 --> 00:22:36.730
We wouldn't be putting out security
updates if it wasn't something that

00:22:36.730 --> 00:22:38.890
we truly felt is in your betterment.

00:22:39.080 --> 00:22:42.440
We're trying to address
identified issues that have arisen

00:22:42.440 --> 00:22:46.580
either that we've identified,
external entities have identified.

00:22:46.580 --> 00:22:50.440
So, as we might say,
heed those security notifications

00:22:50.450 --> 00:22:55.040
from us and update those systems
after you're doing some validation

00:22:55.040 --> 00:22:57.690
internally in your organization.

00:22:57.700 --> 00:23:03.320
The key thing is, the longer you wait
between those updates,

00:23:03.320 --> 00:23:03.320
the longer you're going to have to
wait for the security updates to come.

00:23:03.340 --> 00:23:07.740
So, when you're doing security updates,
when they're available, again,

00:23:07.740 --> 00:23:12.160
is that time that you're potentially
exposing yourselves to vulnerabilities

00:23:12.420 --> 00:23:16.520
once a given vulnerability in a service
or an application has been known,

00:23:16.520 --> 00:23:20.220
the longer you wait,
the longer you expose that system.

