00:42:42.610 --> 00:42:46.320
When connecting to a Wi-Fi access point,
you should always choose the strongest

00:42:46.490 --> 00:42:48.850
wireless security available to you.

00:42:49.090 --> 00:42:54.450
WPA2 provides the strongest
security available on the iPhone.

00:42:54.610 --> 00:42:57.240
You should always choose
this if it's available,

00:42:57.320 --> 00:43:00.050
use the Enterprise Edition when
it's possible,

00:43:00.140 --> 00:43:04.770
and choose EAPTLS or
TTLS for authentication.

00:43:04.940 --> 00:43:08.750
When WPA2 is not available,
